Krasteva, Beloslava (2223) - Francisco Guecamburu, Candela Be (2345) 0-1
Girls World Junior Championship (chess24.com) [11] 2023.10.01
A31 English, symmetrical, Benoni formation

1.d4 Nf6 2.c4 c5 3.Nf3 cxd4 4.Nxd4 b6 5.Nc3 Bb7 6.f3 e6 7.e4 d6 8.Be2 a6 9.Be3 Nbd7 10.O-O Be7 11.Rc1 O-O 12.a3 Qc7 13.b4 Rac8 14.Qb3 Rfe8 15.Rfd1 Qb8 16.Kh1 h5 17.Bf1 h4 18.Qa2 Ne5 19.Na4 Bd8 20.Bg5 h3 21.Bxf6 Bxf6 22.Nxb6 Rcd8 23.Na4 hxg2+ 24.Bxg2 Ng6 25.Qf2 Be5 26.h3 Qc7 27.Ne2 Nf4 28.Nxf4 Bxf4 29.Rc2 Rf8 30.Nb2 f5 31.Nd3 fxe4 32.fxe4 e5 33.Qe2 Bh6 34.Rg1 Bc8 35.c5 Rf6 36.cxd6 Qxd6 37.Nc5 Bf4 38.Rc3 Rh6 39.Rd3 Qxd3 40.Nxd3 Bxh3 41.Bxh3 Rxh3+ 42.Kg2 Rdxd3 43.Qa2+ Kh8 44.Qb1 Rh2+ 45.Kf1 Rc3 46.a4 Rc1+ 47.Qxc1 Bxc1 48.Rg6 Rb2 49.Rb6 Bd2 50.b5 axb5 51.axb5 Be3 52.Rb8+ Kh7 53.Ke1 g5

00:00 Hello Everyone!

The Girls World Junior Championship is an 11-round Swiss tournament taking place September 21-October 1, 2023 in Mexico City, Mexico.

Players receive 90 minutes for 40 moves, followed by 30 minutes to the end of the game, plus a 30-second increment starting from move one. Official website: juniorchesschampionship.fenamacajedrez.com/en/
